</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/27/01 12:04:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Make money fast! ;)</span><hr size=1> We used a similar tactic on the Rathe HGs when we where low 30s. 2 wizzy, 2 pali, 1 war, 1 cleric. Me and the other wizzy would stand a few hundered feet apart. One would nuke and draw agro - palis ans war chase it around whackin his ankles. Wizzy #2 nukes until he draws agro. Repeat until dead, use about a bub of mana, maybe a little bit more. Most of the time, cleric would just nuke since no one was getting hit. <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Channeler of the 51st Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><p>
<span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Moordian Killbringer<br>Warrior of 26 Battle Scars</b><br><i>Dwarven LaMachine of Death</i><br><span style="font-size: 12px; font-famliy: arial">proud member of Infinity Watch - Terris-Thule server</span></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=berdug0>berdug0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/9/01 7:57:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Make money fast! ;)</span><hr size=1> I've been using this tactic for more than 12 levels now.  I just need to tell you that some people don't enjoy beating on a mobs back.  Those silly warriors complain that it's a cheesy tactic since they feel like a Necro pet and that they would rather stand toe to toe to a mob than hit it on the back.  <br>
<br>
Word of warning... this strat doesn't work on the undead.  The undead attack the closest player, not the player doing the most damage.<br>
